News Release









 








Thu, 01 November 2007

2007-137pc
Allison Transmission Appoints David S. Graziosi Chief Financial Officer 

Speedway, IN - Allison Transmission, a market leading global designer and manufacturer of automatic transmissions and hybrid propulsion systems for medium- and heavy-duty commercial trucks, buses, off-road equipment and military vehicles, today announced that David S. Graziosi has been appointed Chief Financial Officer.  Mr. Graziosi, who succeeds interim-CFO John L. Hazen, will begin his duties later this month.“David has an excellent financial and operational background and a proven track record as a CFO,” said Lawrence E. Dewey, Chief Executive Officer of Allison Transmission. “He possesses the leadership skills, the vision and the expertise to manage our Finance function, and together with the rest of our leadership team, will help guide our company successfully through the next phase of our growth and development.”Mr. Graziosi most recently served as Executive Vice President and CFO at Covalence Specialty Materials Corp., a global manufacturer and supplier of plastics, adhesives and packaging products. Prior to that, he held the same position at Resolution Performance Products LLC, a global manufacturer and supplier of epoxy resin and related products for industrial applications. Before joining RPP, Mr. Graziosi spent ten years at several global operating companies where he held numerous financial leadership roles, and six years in public accounting.“I am pleased to join Allison Transmission and am impressed by the strength of the company’s brand, product portfolio and market presence," said Mr. Graziosi. "Allison enjoys leading positions in nearly all of the diverse end markets it serves. With favorable trends toward automaticity in the commercial vehicle industry and the best-in-class automatic product line, Allison’s prospects are stronger than ever. I look forward to working with Allison’s global management team to further strengthen the company’s finance organization and capabilities and to position Allison for continued growth as a stand-alone company.”
* * * * *About Allison TransmissionAllison Transmission (www.allisontransmission.com) is the leading global designer, manufacturer and supplier of automatic transmissions and hybrid propulsion systems for medium- and heavy-duty commercial trucks, buses, off-road equipment and military vehicles, and RVs. The company, headquartered in Speedway, Indiana, employs approximately 3,400 people and sells its transmissions through a worldwide distribution network in North America, South America, Europe, Africa and Asia.
